7. SAFETY AND FAILURE MODES
------------------------------------------------------------

7.1 Designed Safe Failures
- Oracle failure → SafetyKernelTimeout / OracleFeedIdInvalid
- Integrity mismatch → ZTVerificationFailed or Lockout
- Excessive drawdown → Lockout
- MEV spike → MEVPriceSpike
- Cross-feed disagreement → OracleCrossCheckFailed
- Withdrawal before lock → WithdrawalLocked
- Wrong mode withdrawal → WithdrawalModeViolation

7.2 Non-Tolerated Failures
- Silent state corruption
- Unauthorized state mutation
- Bypass of drawdown or lockout logic

These are prevented by:
- Integrity hash
- Mode enforcement
- Policy version enforcement
- Oracle and timing constraints

